<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A6AF4E02-AF19-47EA-BE42-E0E7666019AD" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A6AF4E02-AF19-47EA-BE42-E0E7666019AD" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">16 The function of the knife unit</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The knife unit cuts the media straight. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-2B235171-EA5A-4896-9D36-69E5F4ED1DA0"><title class="- topic/title ">Knife unit (marked yellow)</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-CAA3CEE3-57BE-4E84-BCAA-07BCF34AAE98-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-CAA3CEE3-57BE-4E84-BCAA-07BCF34AAE98-low.png"/></fig><fig class="- topic/fig " id="FIG_3A9106C1B97D40C2AA8F320201CDB8CE"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-349F0D71-DC6C-4D23-A6A6-C305639B46A4-low.png" id="IMAGE_6C98797D58E540D293DA2D783E89E01D" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-349F0D71-DC6C-4D23-A6A6-C305639B46A4-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Attributes</title><p class="- topic/p ">The knife unit consists of the a knife assembly, motor, drive belt and 2 sensors. 
</p><fig id="FIG_875EABC35A144D7EAE97FDA1A294F850" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B4226D53-03DC-43DB-A018-C3895B0D8B6B-low.png" id="IMAGE_B7DFAA0F537545D1A7DF44E1F73B7A5D" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B4226D53-03DC-43DB-A018-C3895B0D8B6B-low.png"/></fig><table id="TABLE_7FEB053F5F784232BAA54690703F4FCF" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remark 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The knife assembly has an upper and lower circular knife to cut the media. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_0AE3BB1A8AB545499C3A619F9CB0D466" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6A1B251D-CFC1-499B-B5EC-FEB03793DDBC-low.png" id="IMAGE_6B28C8C2B9AD4F4E8372AB8847637DF1" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6A1B251D-CFC1-499B-B5EC-FEB03793DDBC-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_6539BEE2144745E09396A0D00CC758C4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-63110E01-D021-4A8B-BC69-751DBB3DC813-low.png" id="IMAGE_1272DBBF1F774C12B0DA26BC2B668F3E" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-63110E01-D021-4A8B-BC69-751DBB3DC813-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media output knife motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 16M2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MOP_KNIFE_MO</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The motor drives the knife though the drive belt. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_9BFEE2319D184766B2DCB29DF31D0C1D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-087DD4A2-DBE2-46FE-9241-37F36920355E-low.png" id="IMAGE_46CA9FB387A24101A2C5D06433B87E9B" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-087DD4A2-DBE2-46FE-9241-37F36920355E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Drive belt 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_5E8D7053DC744722A64DA6112D764C8B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E72ABF8F-7018-44B0-AD8E-5D5D614A33FB-low.png" id="IMAGE_93D3F9E375A445449F795C997474A8E5" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E72ABF8F-7018-44B0-AD8E-5D5D614A33FB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media output knife left sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 16B1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MOP_KNIFE_LEFT_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This sensor detects the leftmost position of the knife. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media output knife right sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 16B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MOP_KNIFE_RIGHT_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This sensor detects the rightmost position of the knife. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_02C348CC203E409CBC617F76BA89C523" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-23EA55A7-E98B-4057-A0AA-AA11580EBDD3-low.png" id="IMAGE_F2CEBC71F9E04F9CAC4530C5532844A3" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-23EA55A7-E98B-4057-A0AA-AA11580EBDD3-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_CA0767495C1F4984BA867E8DB9FD53AD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E7C265FE-793D-47E0-9295-682F034529A1-low.png" id="IMAGE_0AE0D1A4E70C4909B12D5B6BE755A0CA" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E7C265FE-793D-47E0-9295-682F034529A1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">The aluminum frame of the knife unit is mounted with 4 brackets on the print surface. On the frame the motor, sensors, drive belt and knife assembly are mounted. The electrical component and knife assembly are positioned at the left and right hand side of the print surface. 
</p><fig id="FIG_FA311F9D3C7C4BF0A7ED77255CFC14B8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-349F0D71-DC6C-4D23-A6A6-C305639B46A4-low.png" id="IMAGE_2757E144B818462E9C6B4EB1275A7EF5" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-349F0D71-DC6C-4D23-A6A6-C305639B46A4-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The motor drives the drive belt with knife assembly. A drive belt is used to have a correct control of the position of the knife assembly. The media is cut by the upper and lower knife of the knife assembly. The knife cuts only from the home position (motor position) to the other side. After the cut the knife assembly is moved to the home position again. The vane (at the bottom of the knife assembly) activates the sensor at the left or right hand side. 
</p><fig id="FIG_7849BC87935647CEA402E7B0B8E2507C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E7C265FE-793D-47E0-9295-682F034529A1-low.png" id="IMAGE_EF9E5D40041A42118D6304B56F698F24" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E7C265FE-793D-47E0-9295-682F034529A1-low.png"/></fig></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-735E25C2-2936-4ED4-8657-06984403D016.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
